HEADWORD: auxin
<hw>aux"in</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a substance which, in
small concentrations, promotes root formation, bud growth, or certain
other processes such as fruit ripening or leaf drop in plants.</def>⟦br⟧
